_exec_summary.SummaryText:
This summary provides a brief description of the following elements:

    *  The accidental release provision and emergency response policies;
    *  The stationary sources and regulated substances handled;
    *  The worst-case release scenario and the alternative release scenarios, including any administrative 
        controls and mitigation measurers for each scenario;
    *  The general accidental release prevention program and chemical-specific prevention steps;
    *  The five-year accident history;
    *  The emergency response program, and
    *  Planned changes to improve safety.

ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PROVISION AND EMERGENCY RESPONSE

     The DuPont Belle Plant is committed to operating and maintaining all processes in a safe and responsible
manner by adhering to Corporate Policies that embody the following philosophies:

    *  All safety and environmental incidents are preventable;
    *  The goal for safety and environmental incidents is zero: "Zero Incidents, Period";
    *  All employees and contractors are responsible for their safety.

    The DuPont Belle Plant adheres to Corporate Policies embodied in numerous Safety, Health and Environmental (SHE) Standards and Engineering Standards.  The policies are implemented through the Belle Plant Safety, Health and Environmental (SHE) Manual.  This manual is available to all employees.  Included in these standards are the requirements on Process Safety Managements under OSHA.

    Another integral part of the program on accidental release prevention and emergency response is embodied in the guidelines under Responsible Care, a program developed by the American Chemistry Council.

FACILITY DESCRIPTION AND REGULATED SUBSTANCES

   The Dupont Belle Plant manufactures a variety of organic chemicals, agricultural intermediates and agricultural chemicals products.  These include:

      Methylamines (Mono, Di and Tri)             Methacrylic Acid*
      Dimethylformamide (DMF)                      Higher Methacr
